content:
I received a call from an individual named James Wong, who claimed to be from the Ministry of Manpower. He had contacted me using +6591197935. He claimed that workers employed under my details had work permit violations. When I denied knowledge of these workers, the call was transferred via WhatsApp to a second individual named Inspector Timothy Lee, claiming to be from the Singapore Police Force. He instructed me to transfer money to a bank account to support the investigations. 
 As I was scared, I complied with his requests. As a result, I made the following transaction:
 A transaction of $39695.01 was made to TRUST account 28327648 on 2025-07-07.
I realized I had been scammed when the individuals became uncontactable.  I also verified the situation with the Ministry of Manpower and Singapore Police Force, where there were no records of James Wong and Inspector Timothy Lee.
Thank you for providing those details. Could you share any specific URLs or emails that may have been mentioned during the call or communication via WhatsApp?
